If the header text of the BBS is defined as "BayCom-Mailbox" (default after
installation) no automatic mails are generated (for test or user S&F).
\\BULLETIN
A bulletin is a mail to everyone (public mail). It can be read by all stations
but can be only deleted by the sender and/or the BBS sysop. Depending on its
topic it is part of a certain board. It will be deleted when its lifetime has
expired. To send a bulletin you have to use a distribution address, see
HELP ADDRESS.

In contrary to bulletins there are mails to users (user mails). They can be
deleted by the sender, the recipient and the BBS sysop. They have a lifetime,
too.
