\\CONNECT
(SYSOP限定, not possible via air connect)
構文: CONN(ECT) [interface:<hw-addr>] <コール> <digi>

With this command it's possible to connect from sysop console to others. This
possibility is not very comfortable but working. To disconnect use :D command.
If you want to connect via Linux AX25 kernel you have to add interface and
hardware address (call of interface).

例: connect ax25:db0aab-13 oe3dzw db0aab
\\CONVAT
構文: CONV(AT)

Shows file "convat.bcm". This file is used to kick off old areas some BBS
misuse long time.

Example for "convat.bcm":
; Format: <oldat> <newat>
oedl dl
dloe dl
alle dl
oeba dl
all  ww
euro eu
aut  oe

The conversion is only done if bulletins are written local to BBS. Areacode
received via forward will not be changed, but e.g. mail @oedl will be
forwarded like @dl if a conversion @oedl -> @dl is setup in "convat.bcm".
