\\WX
(SYSOP限定, only Linux, init.bcm, option _WXSTN in config.h)
If the WXSTN module is compiled into linux version of OpenBCM, a
wx station of type "Peetbros Ultimeter 2000" (see http://www.peetbros.com)
can be used directly with OpenBCM.

The WX module was developed in 1998 by OE3DZW. It can't be used with
DOS or Windows, only with Linux version!

After starting OpenBCM with WX module the sysop has following new
commands:
- wxtty
- wxstnname
- wxpath
- wxsensoraltitude
- wxqthaltitude

See also HELP WXPATH, HELP WXQTHALTITUDE, HELP WXSENSORALTITUDE,
HELP WXSTNNAME" and HELP WXTTY"
\\WXPATH
(SYSOP限定, only Linux, init.bcm, option _WXSTN in config.h)
構文: WXPATH <path>

Defines the path for the wx data, e.g. "wxpath /bcm/wxdata".

See also HELP WX
\\WXQTHALTITUDE
(SYSOP限定, only Linux, init.bcm, option _WXSTN in config.h)
構文: WXQTHALTITUDE <n>

Defines the altitude <n> in meters of the WX station.

See also HELP WX
\\WXSENSORALTITUDE
(SYSOP限定, only Linux, init.bcm, option _WXSTN in config.h)
構文: WXSENSORALTITUDE <n>

Defines the altitude <n> in meters of the WX station sensor.

See also HELP WX
\\WXSTNNAME
(SYSOP限定, only Linux, init.bcm, option _WXSTN in config.h)
構文: WXSTNNAME <name>

Defines the name of the WX station (max. 30 characters).

See also HELP WX
\\WXTTY
(SYSOP限定, only Linux, init.bcm, option _WXSTN in config.h)
構文: WXTTY <device>

Defines the serial port for the WX station, e.g. "wxtty /dev/ttyS0".

See also HELP WX
\\WYAPP
(SYSOP限定)
構文: WY(APP) <ファイル名>

Writes <filename> with yapp transfer protocol.

See also HELP YAPP
\\YAPP
"Yet Another Protocol" is a comfortable protocol to transmit binary files
via packet radio. It's less known as autobin, but more powerful. User can
use YAPP protocol to up/download files in filesurf mode. Sysops also can
up/download any other files with YAPP protocol.

See also HELP FILESERV YGET, HELP FILESERV YPUT, HELP RYAPP and HELP WYAPP

